      "claim": "If 9 divides 10^n - 1, then 9 divides 10^(n+1) - 1.",
      "reasoning": "We have 10^(n+1) - 1 = 10(10^n - 1) + 9. By the induction hypothesis, 10^n - 1 is divisible by 9, so 10(10^n - 1) is also divisible by 9, and 9 is obviously divisible by 9. Therefore their sum is divisible by 9.",
